ChrisDaubert Chris Daubert (he pronounces it phonetically Doughbear ala the French roots) is the Uncle of Daubert Steven Daubert. He lives in Dixon and is a professional artist. He has made several art exhibits around Davis, notably the wind sensors on the top of the Davis Art Center which would light up lights in one of the rooms as wind would blow over the roof, and currently the Standing Wave at the new explorit science center Explorit building. He has recently picked up Harley Davidson motorcycles as a hobby. Other projects of his include huge topo maps that have an accurate curvature of the earth, and various other metal behemoths. Chris recently undertook a project at the Pence Gallery that was called the hidden.
